body_text.text:
The time trend in Fig. 2
shows that the annual growth rates of GDP and TOUR have experienced similar patterns over the suggested period although growth rates of TOUR were more volatile than GDP (see Table 1
). Specifically, the average quarterly growth rate of GDP was 2.90% with a standard deviation (SD) of 3.61% whereas TOUR was 2.46% with a SD value of 6.76%. The average yearly growth rate of GDP was 12.78%±10.87% (SD) whereas TOUR was 13.03%±16.55% (SD).
